section.def:
constitution
                (章程) means the constitution of the corporation
            for the time being in force;

corporation
                (法團) means the body incorporated by section
                3;

objects
                (宗旨) means the general purposes, aims and objects
            of the corporation as stated in its constitution;

President
                (理事長) means the President of the
            corporation;

paragraph.content:
acquire by purchase, lease or otherwise, and take, hold, enjoy and possess, any
                property, movable or immovable, whether situated in Hong Kong or
                elsewhere;

borrow money in such manner and upon such terms as the corporation may think
                fit, and for that purpose mortgage charge or pledge all or any part of the property
                of the corporation;

appoint such administrative, professional and other officers and staff as the
                corporation deems necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions upon such
                conditions as it thinks fit;

print and publish any periodicals, books, booklets, leaflets or other written
                material that the corporation may think desirable for the promotion of its objects;
                and
